verbs.description: [ARG0: Democrats] [V: have] [ARG1: a slim chance of taking control of the Senate in November 's midterm elections] . Much of that chance rides on the Nevada Senate race , in which Republican Sen. Dean Heller is expected to face Democratic Rep. Jacky Rosen . Rosen still has to clinch the Democratic nomination ; she is facing a group of challengers led by Jesse Sbaih , a largely self - funded candidate who ran against Rosen for her House seat in 2016 . However , with the backing of establishment Democratic leadership , Rosen is considered a heavy favorite in the June 12 primary election . Though Heller is seen as a strong candidate with a reputation for surviving difficult races , a number of factors are leading analysts to say he is vulnerable . The include : Hillary Clinton won Nevada in 2016 ; President Donald Trump continues to have relatively low approval ratings in the Silver State ; Heller 's reputation took a hit last fall when his uncertain stance …
